   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">From the webmanager it is possible to receive different events
and alarms via Modbus and SNMP.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">To change the Modbus or SNMP settings:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the network settings are correctly configured for
your network, see <xref href="GBMS_Network_Settings_CPT_0000527086.dita"
                        scope="local"
                        type="concept"
                        class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Navigate to <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Services &gt; Modbus</uicontrol> or <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Services &gt; SNMP Agent</uicontrol> from the side menu.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Make necessary settings and changes for your network setup.</p>
               <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">Make sure that the Modbus or SNMP settings
confirm to your cyber security policy.</note>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Apply</uicontrol> to confirm any changes.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </p>
